%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20worked%20remotely%20for%20over%207%20years.%20It%20allows%20me%20to%20be%20the%20breadwinner%20of%20our%20family%20and%20be%20a%20more%20present%20mom.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20with%20twins%20posing%20for%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fae5dbf44bdb4cfa383494%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20has%20had%20remote%20jobs%20since%202019.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBack%20in%202013%2C%20before%20the%20pandemic%20made%20remote%20work%20a%20thing%2C%20I%20was%20already%20working%20with%20remote%20teams.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202019%2C%20I%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20go%20fully%20remote%20and%20work%20for%20a%20company%20with%20no%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERemote%20jobs%20have%20allowed%20me%20to%20be%20the%20breadwinner%20while%20also%20being%20a%20present%20mom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-use-google-hangouts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Hangout%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20part%20of%20my%20professional%20career%20since%202013.%20Back%20then%20I%20used%20to%20work%20at%20BuzzFeed%20managing%20operations%20outside%20the%20US%2C%20so%20while%20I%20was%20going%20into%20our%20New%20York%20office%20every%20day%2C%20my%20teams%20were%20all%20remote%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20from%20home%20often%20since%20my%20direct%20reports%20weren't%20physically%20in%20the%20office%20anyway.%20And%20in%202018%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-parent-having-child-early-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20first%20child%20was%20born%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20moved%20into%20a%20hybrid%20schedule%2C%20working%20fully%20from%20home%20two%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-looking-for-work-you-should-volunteer-job-recruiter-says-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfter%20getting%20laid%20off%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20January%202019%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20only%20look%20for%20fully%20remote%20jobs.%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20son%20was%20growing%20too%20quickly%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20a%20part%20of%20his%20life.%20I've%20been%20working%20from%20home%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2254c7aaf4-f713-458b-91aa-4232aad411b6%5C%22%3EPeople%20thought%20I%20was%20a%20freelancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fits-getting-harder-to-find-hybrid-remote-six-figure-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efully%20remote%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20editor%20for%20an%20online%20publication%2C%20everyone%20around%20me%20assumed%20I%20was%20just%20freelancing.%20I%20had%20to%20explain%20over%20and%20over%20again%20that%20the%20company%20had%20no%20physical%20offices%20and%20that%20everyone%20was%20remote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmothers-childcare-working-parents-moms-good-bad-news-why-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMost%20employees%20were%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20were%20attracted%20by%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20flexible%20schedule%20that%20would%20allow%20for%20school%20drop-offs%2C%20having%20a%20sick%20kid%20at%20home%2C%20or%20being%20home%20in%20time%20for%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20joining%2C%20I%20found%20out%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-mother-twins-lacking-connection-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epregnant%20with%20twins%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Being%20pregnant%20takes%20a%20huge%20toll%20on%20your%20body%2C%20but%20being%20pregnant%20with%20twins%20made%20things%20like%20getting%20out%20of%20bed%20feel%20impossible%20at%20times.%20I%20appreciated%20being%20able%20to%20take%20afternoon%20naps%20when%20I%20wasn't%20feeling%20well%2C%20and%20then%20picking%20up%20work%20after%20my%20oldest%20was%20in%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20it%20to%20almost%2039%20weeks%20pregnant%20with%20the%20twins%2C%20and%20I%20credit%20that%20to%20not%20having%20to%20commute%20every%20day%2C%20putting%20my%20body%20through%20the%20stress%20of%20riding%20the%20New%20York%20City%20subway%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22287a59fa-90ba-456e-a3b3-9e79ecd0602c%5C%22%3EI%20moved%20from%20New%20York%20City%20to%20Maine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20remote%20job%20also%20allowed%20my%20family%20to%20move%20from%20our%20tiny%20and%20cramped%20Brooklyn%20apartment%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-nyc-to-portland-maine-differences-surprises-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehouse%20with%20a%20backyard%20in%20Portland%2C%20Maine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20that%20at%20least%20one%20of%20us%20had%20a%20full-time%20job%20that%20we%20could%20take%20everywhere%20we%20went%20made%20the%20decision%20much%20easier.%20And%20it%20has%20been%20incredibly%20beneficial%20for%20our%20family%2C%20especially%20for%20our%20three%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20changed%20jobs%20again%20in%202021%20to%20another%20fully%20remote%20job%2C%20where%20I'm%20once%20again%20remote%20to%20my%20team%20%E2%80%94%20who%20often%20also%20works%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b239c68-889e-49d3-8b23-ed923a58dbf2%5C%22%3EI'm%20a%20more%20present%20parent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20my%20kids%20are%206%2C%204%2C%20and%204%2C%20having%20a%20remote%20job%20is%20invaluable.%20I%20not%20only%20get%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-breadwinner-biggest-misconceptions-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebe%20the%20breadwinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20home%2C%20but%20I%20also%20am%20a%20present%20mom%20to%20our%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20commute%2C%20I%20can%20sit%20down%20for%20breakfast%20with%20them%2C%20drop%20them%20off%20for%20school%2C%20and%20still%20make%20it%20back%20home%20in%20time%20for%20my%20first%20meeting%20an%20hour%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20worked%20in%20offices%2C%20we%20would%20text%20each%20other%20to%20see%20who%20could%20make%20it%20back%20home%20in%20time%20to%20relieve%20our%20nanny%2C%20who%20would%20often%20put%20our%20son%20to%20bed%20because%20we%20would%20work%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20even%20if%20I%20have%20to%20work%20late%20(which%20is%20incredibly%20rare)%2C%20I%20can%20still%20walk%20upstairs%20for%20story%20time%20and%20tuck%20in%20before%20resuming%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20I%20still%20rely%20on%20my%20husband%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20more%20fun%20parenting%20jobs%2C%20like%20taking%20care%20of%20the%20kids%20in%20the%20summer%20when%20school%20is%20closed%20or%20all%20the%20extra%20holidays%20they%20get%20that%20don't%20align%20with%20my%20work%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20I%20remember%20being%20sad%20that%20my%20dad%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20the%20breadwinner%20in%20my%20family%20%E2%80%94%20missed%20so%20much%20of%20my%20childhood%20because%20of%20work.%20It%20makes%20me%20proud%20that%20I%20can%20have%20the%20same%20role%2C%20while%20also%20being%20way%20more%20present%20than%20he%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-job-allows-mom-be-present-while-breadwinner-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727776442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fae5e975c877a99b61da19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-job-allows-mom-be-present-while-breadwinner-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Before%20the%20pandemic%20made%20remote%20work%20a%20thing%2C%20I%20was%20already%20working%20from%20home.%20It's%20allowed%20me%20to%20be%20present%20in%20my%20kids'%20life%20while%20being%20the%20breadwinner.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpreti%40insider.com%20(Conz%20Preti)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-job-allows-mom-be-present-while-breadwinner-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20monitored%20my%20friends'%20phones.%20What%20I%20saw%20horrified%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20wearing%20police%20uniform%20in%20phone%20screen%20holding%20hand%20up%2C%20indicating%20%26quot%3Bstop%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fb17677518aa57bc9f7f91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20iStock%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20and%20I%20are%20probably%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20on%20our%20phones.%20But%20how%20%3Cem%3Emuch%3C%2Fem%3E%20time%20is%20%3Cem%3Etoo%20%3C%2Fem%3Emuch%3F%20Ever%20since%20Apple%20rolled%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-iphone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPhone's%3C%2Fa%3E%20screen-time%20tracking%20feature%20in%202018%2C%20we've%20been%20shocked%20and%20ashamed%20to%20see%20how%20many%20minutes%20and%20hours%20we%20spend%20basking%20in%20the%20screen's%20LED%20glow.%20But%20that%20number%20doesn't%20tell%20me%20if%20my%20four%20hours%20a%20day%20(which%20sounds%20like%20a%20lot)%20is%20a%20heroic%20feat%20of%20restraint%20and%20time%20well%20spent%20or%20a%20sign%20that%20I'm%20scrolling%20life%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20I%20ended%20up%20trying%20out%20Clearspace%2C%20one%20of%20several%20apps%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20take%20control%20of%20their%20screen%20time%2C%20and%20perhaps%20the%20most%20brazen%20of%20them.%20Clearspace%2C%20backed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-making-first-weapons-industry-bet-on-missile-startup-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EY%20Combinator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20only%20lets%20you%20restrict%20how%20many%20times%20you%20open%20an%20app%20each%20day%20but%20is%20testing%20a%20new%20feature%20that%20lets%20you%20see%20how%20much%20time%20your%20friends%20are%20spending%20on%20their%20phones.%20Screen-time%20creeping%20has%20entered%20the%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20sign%20up%2C%20you%20can%20opt%20to%20give%20yourself%20a%20set%20number%20of%20times%20you're%20allowed%20to%20open%20certain%20apps%20in%20a%20day.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20let%20myself%20open%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-tiktok-ban-marketers-employees-creators-are-not-worried-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20six%20times%20(probably%20a%20generously%20low%20guess%20on%20the%20number%20of%20times%20I%20was%20clicking%20the%20app%20daily)%20and%20gave%20myself%20three%20times%20to%20open%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-new-ray-ban-smart-glasses-apple-vision-pro-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20home%20of%20my%20favorite%20serotonin-boosting%20activity%3A%20mindlessly%20scrolling%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20for%20cheap%20home%20goods.%20While%20I'd%20prefer%20to%20open%20Slack%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgmail-update-fix-email-tabbed-inbox-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGmail%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20often%20than%20I%20do%2C%20I'd%20also%20prefer%20to%20keep%20my%20job.%20Each%20time%20I%20wanted%20to%20browse%20secondhand%20shoe%20racks%2C%20before%20I%20could%20open%20Facebook%2C%20Clearspace%20prompted%20me%20to%20take%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20read%20an%20inspirational-poster%20quote%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%26quot%3BHowever%20little%20television%20you%20watch%2C%20watch%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20credited%20to%20the%20historian%20David%20McCullough%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BWonder%20is%20the%20very%20engine%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20explorer%20Erling%20Kagge.%20Then%20I%20could%20select%20how%20long%20I'd%20like%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20app%20(10%20minutes%20at%20most)%20before%20I'd%20be%20kicked%20out.%20For%20TikTok%2C%20that%20was%20a%20helpful%20nudge%20back%20into%20the%20real%20world.%20For%20The%20New%20York%20Times'%20games%20app%2C%20it%20filled%20me%20with%20ire%3B%20I%20can't%20do%20a%20Sunday%20crossword%20in%2010-minute%20increments.%20Off%20the%20restricted%20list%20it%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20weren't%20exactly%20thrilled%20to%20join%20my%20experiment.%20One%20downloaded%20it%2C%20restricted%20TikTok%2C%20and%20then%20texted%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20currently%20scrolling%20on%20TikTok%20and%20plan%20to%20all%20day.%20It%20better%20not%20stop%20me.%26quot%3B%20When%20the%20app%20ultimately%20did%2C%20I%20could%20see%20that%20she%20deleted%20TikTok%20from%20her%20restricted%20apps%2C%20added%20Duolingo%2C%20and%20clocked%20nine%20hours%20of%20screen%20time%20that%20day%20and%2010%20the%20next%2C%20an%20amount%20that%20both%20stunned%20and%20impressed%20me%2C%20given%20she%20has%20a%20full-time%20office%20job.%20(When%20confronted%2C%20she%20blamed%20the%20high%20screen%20time%20on%20her%20Kindle%20app%20and%20podcasts.)%20It%20doesn't%20appear%20she%20ever%20opened%20Duolingo%2C%20so%20I%20won't%20expect%20to%20see%20any%20sudden%20improvements%20in%20her%20Spanish%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoyce%20Branning%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Clearspace%2C%20says%20the%20company%20started%20testing%20the%20friends%20feature%20after%20hearing%20that%20users%20were%20taking%20screenshots%20of%20their%20Clearspace%20screen%20tracking%20and%20sharing%20it%20with%20one%20another.%20That%20can%20open%20up%20conversation%2C%20as%20it%20did%20when%20I%20asked%20my%20friend%20how%20she%20spent%2010%20hours%20on%20her%20phone%20in%20day.%20Branning%20says%20that%20building%20the%20feature%20into%20the%20app%20is%20a%20way%20to%20%26quot%3Barm%20people's%20little%20community%20with%20the%20ability%20to%20encourage%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20compete.%20Branning%20says%20he%20and%20his%20cofounder%20use%20it%20to%20keep%20each%20other%20accountable%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20sense%20of%20friendly%20competition.%20Still%2C%20they%20don't%20think%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20get%20screen%20time%20down%20to%20the%20lowest%20possible%20levels.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20think%20screen%20time%20is%20inherently%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20Branning%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20reduce%20regrettable%20usage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20sure%20where%20my%20friends%20spent%20all%20their%20screen%20time%2C%20but%20being%20on%20a%20phone%20doesn't%20inherently%20ruin%20your%20life.%20Sharing%20memes%20is%20how%20I%20bond%20with%20my%20friends.%20Procuring%20the%20perfect%20used%20plant%20stand%20from%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20requires%20constant%20vigilance%2C%20and%20when%20I%20finally%20see%20that%20trendy%20item%20I've%20been%20looking%20for%20marked%20down%20to%20%2420%2C%20it's%20a%20cosmic%20thrill.%20And%20I'm%20sure%20that%20breaking%20news%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-mayor-eric-adams-charges-indicted-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eindictment%20of%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20%26quot%3BTrash%20Revolution%26quot%3B%20Adams%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20my%20screen%20time%20and%20X%20usage%20to%20skyrocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Jason%20Nagata%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20pediatrics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20says%20one%20of%20the%20big%20problems%20with%20staying%20surgically%20attached%20to%20your%20phone%20is%20that%20the%20screen%20is%20often%20replacing%20something%20else%20in%20your%20life.%20If%20you're%20scrolling%20Instagram%20and%20TikTok%20for%20hours%20instead%20of%20exercising%20or%20meeting%20up%20with%20friends%2C%20you%20may%20be%20swapping%20healthy%20activities%20with%20sedentary%20and%20anxiety-inducing%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20research%20about%20the%20negative%20effects%20of%20screen%20time%20focuses%20on%20children%20rather%20than%20adults.%20While%20kids%20are%20using%20screens%20increasingly%20often%20to%20learn%2C%20excessively%20staring%20at%20them%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20lower%20cognitive%20abilities.%20For%20adolescents%2C%20social-media%20use%20can%20contribute%20to%20insecurities%2C%20body-image%20issues%2C%20and%20eating%20disorders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20screen%20time%20even%20children%20should%20be%20allotted%20has%20gotten%20murkier.%20The%20American%20Academy%20of%20Pediatrics%20recommended%20limiting%20screen%20time%20to%20two%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20but%20in%202016%20it%20did%20away%20with%20the%20hard%20line%2C%20instead%20guiding%20caregivers%20to%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bmindful%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20screens.%20Experts%20don't%20really%20know%20how%20much%20screen%20time%20is%20too%20much%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20makes%20the%20minutes%20and%20hours%20ticking%20up%20on%20screen-time%20apps%20harder%20to%20decipher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScreen-time%20apps%20like%20Clearspace%2C%20OffScreen%2C%20AppBlock%2C%20and%20slew%20of%20others%20designed%20for%20parents%20to%20set%20limits%20for%20their%20children%20might%20be%20useful%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20on%20their%20own%20be%20a%20fix%20for%20excessive%20scrolling.%20Nagata%20says%20there%20has%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bsome%20sort%20of%20buy-in%26quot%3B%20and%20desire%20to%20reduce%20screen%20time.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20a%20tool%20to%20limit%20your%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20My%20friends%20lacked%20the%20willpower%2C%20and%20the%20openness%2C%20to%20fully%20buy%20in.%20One%20immediately%20refused%20to%20download%20it%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20results%20would%20make%20her%20feel%20too%20guilty%20and%20that%20she%20doesn't%20look%20at%20her%20screen%20time.%20Another%20said%20she%20planned%20to%20delete%20it%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20trial%20for%20new%20features%20expired%20(after%20which%20Clearspace%20charges%20%2450%20a%20year%20for%20its%20premium%20version)%20and%20found%20the%20app-opening%20limits%20annoying.%20And%20I%20don't%20think%20my%20first%20friend%20paid%20much%20attention%20to%20%3Cem%3Emy%3C%2Fem%3E%20screen%20time%20%E2%80%94%20she%20was%20clearly%20busy%20doing%20other%20things%20with%20her%20phone%20for%20nine%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBranning%20tells%20me%20he%20imagined%20people%20would%20share%20their%20screen-time%20totals%20with%20very%20close%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20people%20they%20share%20their%20location%20with.%20His%20hunch%20was%20right%3A%20I%20already%20share%20my%20location%20with%20the%20friends%20I%20had%20try%20the%20app%2C%20and%20I%20find%20myself%20checking%20to%20see%20where%20they%20are%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20even%20though%20we%20live%20in%20different%20cities.%20Watching%20their%20screen%20time%20tick%20up%20gives%20me%20another%20glimpse%20into%20what%20they're%20doing%20when%20we're%20apart%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20further%20breakdown%20of%20their%20private%20actions%20that%20I%20really%20don't%20need.%20Maybe%20my%20friend%20who%20didn't%20want%20to%20join%20us%20was%20onto%20something%20about%20keeping%20her%20scrolling%20a%20secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20less%20the%20peer%20pressure%20and%20the%20more%20the%20irritation%20of%20waiting%20for%20the%20app%20to%20open%20(and%20being%20reminded%20that%20there%20are%20other%20things%20I%20could%20do%20with%20my%20time)%20that%20got%20me%20to%20spend%20less%20time%20scrolling.%20The%20icons%20of%20the%20apps%20I%20chose%20to%20limit%20were%20shaded%20on%20my%20screen%2C%20deterring%20me%20from%20clicking%20and%20undergoing%20another%20breathing%20exercise%20before%20opening%20them.%20I%20stuck%20to%20my%20limits%20every%20day%20%E2%80%94%20even%20clocking%20in%20below%20them.%20And%20after%20the%20first%20day%2C%20I%20did%20find%20myself%20less%20inclined%20to%20spend%20time%20on%20TikTok%20than%20before%2C%20but%20I%20watched%20more%20Instagram%20reels%2C%20which%20are%20just%20less-funny%20TikToks%20or%20videos%20I%20already%20saw%20on%20TikTok%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20logging%20in%20to%20an%20app%20like%20Clearspace%20with%20friends%2C%20family%2C%20and%20romantic%20partners%20could%20help%20people%20police%20each%20other.%20Perhaps%20you'd%20think%20twice%20before%20opening%20TikTok%20for%20the%2018th%20time%20on%20a%20Wednesday%20knowing%20that%20judgmental%20eyes%20could%20be%20lurking.%20As%20for%20me%2C%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20pay%20too%20much%20attention%20to%20the%20number%20of%20times%20I%20pick%20up%20my%20phone%20or%20how%20long%20I'm%20on%20TikTok.%20And%20I'll%20definitely%20be%20going%20back%20to%20doomscrolling%20in%20private.%20Ultimately%2C%20we%20may%20want%20to%20prioritize%20limiting%20how%20much%20we%20know%20about%20each%20other%20than%20limiting%20our%20screen%20time.%20Knowing%20less%20about%20everyone's%20business%20leaves%20more%20room%20to%20wonder%2C%20which%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20the%20very%20engine%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727776322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fb16e275c877a99b620099%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Addicted%20to%20your%20phone%3F%20A%20new%20app%20lets%20your%20friends%20stage%20an%20intervention.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20brother%20and%20I%20were%20born%2016%20years%20apart.%20We%20had%20different%20childhoods%2C%20but%20we've%20realized%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20in%20common.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nia%20Springer-Norris%20with%20her%20brother%2C%20Winston%2C%20sitting%20at%20a%20restaurant.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66faaaacf44bdb4cfa3809f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENia%20Springer-Norris%20and%20her%20brother%20Winston%20are%2016%20years%20apart%20in%20age.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Nia%20Springer-Norris%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20brother%20is%2016%20years%20younger%20than%20I%20am%2C%20and%20we%20rarely%20lived%20in%20the%20same%20place%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20had%20a%20very%20different%20childhood%20than%20I%20did%2C%20and%20we%20had%20different%20parents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20over%20the%20years%2C%20we've%20realized%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20in%20common.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%2013%2C%20Winston%20was%20already%20taller%20than%20me.%20I%20found%20this%20out%20at%20my%20wedding%20%E2%80%94%20my%20younger%20brother%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20taller%20than%20my%20husband.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20we%20hadn't%20seen%20each%20other%20since%20four%20years%20prior%2C%20when%20our%20grandmother%20brought%20him%20to%20visit%20me%20in%20Asheville%2C%20North%20Carolina.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%2016%20when%20Winston%20was%20born%2C%20already%20on%20my%20way%20out%20of%20the%20house%20as%20he%20was%20coming%20into%20the%20world.%20His%20birth%20was%20a%20surprise%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonly-child-had-multiple-under-3-years-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealbeit%20a%20welcome%20one%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b7c76e9-c1df-4dc6-a364-f0e6cffd3f17%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20had%20different%20childhoods%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20defiant%20but%20smart%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-has-had-kids-in-private-public-and-homeschool-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etransferred%20to%20a%20public%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20my%20junior%20year%20when%20the%20prep%20school%20I%20attended%20did%20not%20invite%20me%20to%20return%20at%20the%20end%20of%2010th%20grade.%20I%20was%20eager%20to%20grow%20up%20and%20ready%20to%20be%20done%20%E2%80%94%20I%20ran%20away%20from%20home%20for%20a%20full%20week%20that%20fall.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EComing%20home%2C%20I%20wanted%20a%20way%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20I%20set%20my%20mind%20to%20something%2C%20I%20do%20it.%20I%20finagled%20an%20early%20graduation%20by%20taking%20a%20class%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20for%20my%20final%20English%20credit%20and%20dropping%20my%20lunch%20period%20to%20take%20the%20mandatory%20fourth%20year%20of%20PE.%20I%20was%20accepted%20to%20Chatham%20College%20(now%20Chatham%20University).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWinston%20was%20barely%20a%20year%20old%20when%20I%20graduated%20and%20began%20to%20prepare%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20house.%20Then%2C%20my%20parents%20moved%20to%20London%20during%20my%20freshman%20year%2C%20and%20we%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-daughter-long-distance-living-abroad-closer-relationship-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%20different%20continents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20had%20very%20different%20childhoods%20with%20very%20different%20parents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20kid%20in%20the%2090s%20with%20two%20moms%20in%20an%20interracial%20relationship%2C%20my%20existence%20perplexed%20my%20peers.%20They%20asked%20how%20I%20was%20conceived%20and%20assumed%20that%20my%20Mama%20Casi%20(who%20passed%20in%20April)%20was%20my%20biological%20mom%20because%20I%20look%20white.%20My%20moms%20split%20when%20I%20was%208%2C%20and%20my%20birth%20mom%20met%20my%20stepdad%2C%20Norman%2C%20Win's%20father.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20mom%20was%2038%20when%20she%20became%20pregnant%20with%20my%20brother.%20She%20had%20more%20life%20experience%2C%20which%20nurtured%20new%20perspectives%20on%20parenting.%20I%20went%20to%20multiple%20schools%20while%20Win%20was%20homeschooled.%20I%20received%20an%20exceptional%20traditional%20education.%20Win%20was%20able%20to%20explore%20his%20interests%20in-depth%20and%20started%20his%20business%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackdreamescape.com%2Fhome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBlack%20Dream%20Escape%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20before%20he%20turned%2018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221544%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nia%20Springer-Norris%20with%20her%20birth%20mom%20and%20Winston's%20step%20dad%2C%20holding%20Winston%2C%20standing%20outside%20in%20a%20courtyard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66faaafbf44bdb4cfa380a6f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3