%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fae16df44bdb4cfa382f44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsibling-age-gap-birth-order-common-ground-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20brother%20and%20I%20are%2016%20years%20apart%20in%20age.%20We%20had%20different%20childhoods%20and%20rarely%20lived%20in%20the%20same%20place%2C%20but%20we%20realized%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20in%20common.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Nia%20Springer-Norris)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsibling-age-gap-birth-order-common-ground-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boomers%20are%20selling%20off%20their%20businesses.%20Millennials%20are%20swooping%20in.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stock%20graph%20with%20younger%20woman%20and%20older%20woman%20on%20opposite%20ends%20of%20the%20upward%20arrow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f72610f9f6733e4be08cee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20iStock%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20George%20Coulam%20decided%20to%20retire%2C%20he%20had%20a%20problem.%20He%20owned%20the%20Texas%20Renaissance%20Festival%20%E2%80%94%20which%20bills%20itself%20as%20the%20largest%20such%20gathering%20in%20America%2C%20drawing%20over%20500%2C000%20annual%20visitors%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20successor.%20Several%20longtime%20associates%20were%20eager%20to%20take%20over%2C%20but%20Coulam%20had%20run%20the%20fair%20for%20decades%3B%20he%20wanted%20his%20pride%20and%20joy%20to%20land%20in%20the%20right%20hands.%20Suitor%20after%20suitor%20put%20in%20bids%20to%20buy%20the%20business%2C%20but%20none%20felt%20like%20the%20right%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20US%2C%20older%20business%20owners%20are%20arriving%20at%20the%20same%20juncture.%20Over%20half%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-small-business-owner-economy-interest-rate-cuts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20those%20with%20a%20single%20owner%20and%20fewer%20than%20500%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20are%20owned%20by%20people%20over%2050.%20The%20wealth-management%20firm%20NewEdge%20Wealth%20has%20estimated%20that%20boomer-owned%20businesses%20in%20the%20US%20are%20worth%20about%20%2410%20trillion.%20Those%20boomers%20can't%20retire%20and%20enjoy%20their%20sunset%20years%20until%20they%20figure%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentrepreneurs-small-business-owners-share-challenges-of-starting-company-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20to%20do%20with%20their%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Can%20a%20relative%20or%20longtime%20employee%20take%20over%3F%20Should%20they%20shut%20down%3F%20Or%20can%20they%20sell%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20millennials%20with%20the%20entrepreneurial%20bug%2C%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomer%20retirement%20bomb%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20a%20boon.%20As%20they%20enter%20their%20prime%20wealth-building%20years%2C%20many%20are%20anxious%20about%20how%20they'll%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-millennials-need-for-retirement-savings-strategies-401k-ira-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esave%20up%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-sellers-summer-disappointment-mortgage-rates-house-prices-real-estate-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturbulent%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20buying%20an%20existing%20business%20offers%20a%20tantalizing%20opportunity.%20The%20market-research%20firm%20Forrester%20found%20in%20a%20survey%20it%20conducted%20last%20year%20that%2064%25%20of%20people%20buying%20businesses%20were%20millennials%20or%20younger.%20Sure%2C%20many%20small%20businesses%20aren't%20glamorous%20%E2%80%94%20think%20dental%20practices%20or%20accounting%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20involve%20long%20hours%20and%20unpredictable%20market%20forces.%20But%20they%20might%20just%20be%20a%20better%20pathway%20to%20retirement%20than%20building%20a%20business%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-startups-get-bought-up-by-private-equity-vc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20seen%20the%20wisdom%20in%20acquiring%20small%20businesses.%20Why%20should%20they%20be%20the%20only%20ones%20reaping%20the%20fruits%20of%20boomer%20labor%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20Nancy%20Forster-Holt%2C%20an%20accountant%20at%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young%2C%20was%20transferred%20from%20Sacramento%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Maine.%20She%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20state%20and%20her%20now-husband%2C%20Steve%20Holt.%20They%20decided%20to%20buy%20a%20business%20together.%20Since%20she%20had%20experience%20as%20a%20chief%20financial%20officer%20and%20he%20was%20an%20engineer%2C%20they%20focused%20on%20manufacturing%20companies.%20They%20soon%20found%20Shaw%20%26amp%3B%20Tenney%2C%20a%20century-and-a-half-old%20manufacturer%20of%20wooden%20paddles%20and%20oars%20in%20Orono.%20Before%20the%20Holts%20bought%20it%20in%202003%2C%20Shaw%20%26amp%3B%20Tenney%20had%20had%20only%20two%20other%20owners%3A%20the%20Tenney%20family%2C%20which%20operated%20it%20until%201978%2C%20and%20Paul%20and%20Helen%20Reagan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20decided%20to%20retire%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Holts%20thought%20their%20children%20might%20want%20to%20take%20over.%20But%20no%20one%20showed%20any%20interest.%20%26quot%3BThey%20all%20grew%20up%20in%20it%20and%20worked%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Forster-Holt%2C%20who's%20also%20a%20clinical%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Rhode%20Island's%20business%20school%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BOur%20last%20one%20graduated%20in%202022%2C%20and%20he's%20a%20food%20scientist%2C%20and%20we're%20a%20manufacturer%20of%20oars%20and%20paddles.%26quot%3B%20The%20couple%20realized%20they%20had%20to%20sell%2C%20and%20they%20started%20marketing%20the%20company%20while%20planning%20the%20graduation%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20Jennifer%20and%20Neil%20Gutekunst%20came%20along.%20When%20they%20acquired%20Shaw%20%26amp%3B%20Tenney%20in%202023%2C%20they%20had%20two%20other%20small%20businesses%20under%20their%20belt.%20They%20took%20what%20the%20Holts%20built%20%E2%80%94%20a%20recognized%20brand%2C%20equipment%2C%20a%20highly%20skilled%20workforce%2C%20and%20customer%20relationships%20%E2%80%94%20and%20ran%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20businesses%20we%20purchased%20all%20had%20cash%20day%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Neil%20Gutekunst%20said.%20Neither%20of%20the%20Gutekunsts%20had%20a%20sales%20background%2C%20but%20the%20three%20companies%20they%20purchased%20had%20strong%20customer%20bases%20and%20solid%20reputations.%20All%20they%20had%20to%20do%20was%20keep%20things%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20said%20in%20July%20that%20there%20were%20nearly%2035%20million%20small%20businesses%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20those%2C%2082%25%2C%20had%20no%20employees%20other%20than%20the%20owner%2C%20meaning%20they%20probably%20wouldn't%20make%20sense%20to%20sell.%20But%20each%20year%2C%20about%2065%2C000%20of%20the%20remaining%20chunk%20of%20businesses%20are%20listed%20on%20BizBuySell%2C%20an%20online%20listing%20service%20of%20businesses%20for%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEdie%20Ellis%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20consulting%20firm%20in%20Chicago%20and%20has%20advised%20industrial%20companies%20on%20acquisitions%2C%20said%20the%20peak%20of%20small-business%20sales%20began%20when%20baby%20boomers%20started%20to%20turn%2060%2C%20in%20about%202006.%20Many%20owners%20found%20that%20their%20children%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20over%2C%20so%20they%20looked%20for%20buyers.%20The%20kids%20of%20small-business%20owners%20%26quot%3Brun%20the%20opposite%20direction%2C%20because%20they%20saw%20the%20lifestyle%2C%26quot%3B%20Ellis%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20saw%20that%20mom%20and%20dad%20worked%2024%2F7%2C%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20weekend%20off%2C%20you%20know%3F%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FOAkGr%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Number%20of%20small%20businesses%20sold%20per%20quarter%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20BizBuySell%20indicates%20that%20sales%20of%20small%20businesses%20have%20been%20lower%20since%20the%202006%20peak%20and%20dipped%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20quarterly%20transaction%20volume%20has%20largely%20recovered%20from%202020%20and%20has%20held%20steady.%20In%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year%2C%20BizBuySell%20had%20listings%20for%20over%2035%2C000%20businesses%20with%20a%20median%20asking%20price%20of%20%24395%2C000%20and%20a%20median%20revenue%20of%20over%20%24700%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20meanwhile%2C%20in%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20the%20median%20home%20price%20recently%20hit%20%24412%2C000.%20Demand%20for%20these%20businesses%20is%20growing%2C%20pushing%20the%20median%20sales%20price%20up%2025%25%20over%20last%20year.%20While%20not%20all%20of%20these%20companies%20will%20be%20a%20good%20investment%2C%20the%20right%20venture%20could%20offer%20an%20edge%20over%20more%20traditional%20wealth-building%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upside%20of%20buying%20an%20existing%20small%20business%2C%20besides%20inheriting%20foundational%20elements%20%E2%80%94%20a%20brand%2C%20suppliers%2C%20systems%2C%20and%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20financing%20an%20acquisition%20is%20often%20easier%20than%20financing%20a%20brand-new%20business.%20You%20don't%20need%20to%20have%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20in%20cash%20on%20hand%20to%20take%20advantage.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20sellers%20are%20willing%20to%20assist%20in%20financing%20because%20they%20want%20the%20business%20out%20of%20their%20hands.%20Some%20will%20accept%20deferred%20compensation%20or%20a%20share%20of%20future%20earnings%20as%20a%20way%20to%20lessen%20the%20up-front%20cost.%20Buyers%20with%20good%20credit%20can%20also%20borrow%20money%20through%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExisting%20companies%20often%20have%20assets%20that%20can%20help%20make%20financing%20easier.%20If%20the%20business%20owns%20land%2C%20buildings%2C%20or%20equipment%2C%20that%20can%20serve%20as%20collateral%20for%20a%20bank%20loan.%20Plus%2C%20with%20revenue%20already%20coming%20in%20the%20door%2C%20lenders%20know%20they%20won't%20have%20to%20wait%20to%20receive%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20are%20some%20logistical%20challenges%20in%20finding%20the%20right%20business%20%E2%80%94%20fewer%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20businesses%20listed%20on%20BizBuySell%20sell%20in%20a%20given%20year.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20great%20small%20businesses%20aren't%20always%20in%20places%20where%20people%20want%20to%20move.%20Dave%20Specht%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Drucker%20School%20Global%20Family%20Business%20Institute%20at%20Claremont%20Graduate%20University%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20situation%20is%20compounded%20when%20people%20in%20small%20towns%20don't%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20their%20neighbors%20about%20their%20plans%20for%20their%20businesses.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20great%20secrecy%20around%20the%20timing%20of%20transitions%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Specht%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20small%20town%20in%20Washington%2C%20said.%20Often%2C%20potential%20buyers%20end%20up%20looking%20elsewhere.%20%26quot%3BThey%20go%20to%20a%20larger%20town%20or%20a%20larger%20city%20because%20they%20just%20don't%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20businesses%20need%20a%20buyer%20with%20a%20combination%20of%20skills%20that%20isn't%20easy%20to%20find.%20Some%20have%20real%20estate%20that's%20worth%20more%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20assets.%20And%20some%20are%20%26quot%3Blifestyle%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20bookstores%2C%20yarn%20stores%2C%20and%20other%20Main%20Street%20businesses%2C%20that%20don't%20generate%20much%20profit%20beyond%20the%20owner's%20small%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20businesses%20might%20have%20hidden%20problems%2C%20Ellis%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHave%20they%20been%20paying%20their%20bills%3F%20Have%20they%20been%20paying%20the%20IRS%3F%20You%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20don't%20stop%20once%20you've%20made%20the%20purchase.%20Fewer%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20small%20businesses%20in%20the%20US%20in%202022%20were%20profitable%2C%20and%20over%20a%20million%20businesses%20of%20all%20sizes%20close%20each%20year.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20people%20that%20come%20up%20from%20Wall%20Street%20and%20they%20want%20to%20buy%20a%20bed-and-breakfast%20in%20Maine%20because%20they've%20always%20loved%20Maine%2C%26quot%3B%20Forster-Holt%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20guess%20what%3F%20They're%20working%2024%2F7%2C%20365%2C%20helping%20other%20people%20enjoy%20Maine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20noticed%20that%20people%20with%20experience%20working%20in%20corporations%20sometimes%20struggle%20with%20the%20flat%20hierarchy%20and%20ever-changing%20priorities%20of%20a%20small%20business.%20%26quot%3BYou%20come%20to%20work%20and%20you've%20got%20your%20to-do%20list%2C%20and%20a%20truck%20has%20hit%20your%20building%2C%20and%20now%20your%20day%20is%20something%20completely%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20the%20temperament%20for%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Holts%20found%20that%20they%20did.%20%26quot%3BI%20loved%20working%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Forster-Holt%20told%20me.%20And%20those%20who%20can%20roll%20with%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20upheaval%20can%20reap%20the%20financial%20upsides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-deals-private-equity-acquihires-ai-tech-vc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20certainly%20familiar%20with%20those%20upsides.%20The%20American%20Investment%20Council%20reported%20that%2085%25%20of%20private-equity%20investments%20in%202022%20were%20small%20businesses.%20Citing%20the%20data%20provider%20Preqin%2C%20PwC%20recently%20reported%20that%2C%20as%20of%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20private%20equity%20firms%20had%20%241%20trillion%20in%20liquid%20assets%20that%20were%20looking%20for%20investments.%20These%20companies%20are%20interested%20in%20small%20businesses%20that%20operate%20similarly%20in%20many%20markets%20and%20can%20be%20rolled%20up%20together%2C%20such%20as%20plumbing%20or%20HVAC%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrivate%20equity%20is%20smart%20in%20targeting%20family%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Specht%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BMany%20of%20them%20are%20great%20businesses.%26quot%3B%20Fortunately%20for%20millennial%20buyers%2C%20many%20family%20owners%20would%20prefer%20not%20to%20deal%20with%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Dinkel's%20Bakery%2C%20a%20beloved%20Chicago%20institution%2C%20closed%20after%20a%20century%20in%20business.%20Norm%20Dinkel%2C%20the%20third-generation%20owner%2C%20wanted%20to%20retire%2C%20and%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblockclubchicago.org%2F2022%2F04%2F05%2Fdinkels-bakery-is-closing-after-100-years-on-the-north-side%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR0BZXSbl9TRiwoiT-brphpBBhEbM9RU9LgMygGULYZg0kNZpESJxBYUxyU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecouldn't%20find%20a%20buyer%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20also%20wanted%20to%20operate%20the%20business.%20Anyone%20fortunate%20enough%20to%20have%20had%20a%20Dinkel's%20chocolate%20doughnut%20or%20fresh%20strawberry%20paczki%20knows%20the%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20small%20businesses%20were%20family%20businesses%2C%20and%20the%20eldest%20male%20child%20was%20expected%20to%20take%20it%20over%20when%20the%20patriarch%20was%20ready%20to%20step%20down.%20That%20got%20Dinkel's%20through%20a%20hundred%20years%20of%20operation.%20Many%20small-business%20owners%20want%20to%20keep%20the%20company%20in%20the%20family%2C%20said%20Brian%20Brogan%2C%20who%20works%20as%20a%20wealth%20advisor%20to%20family-business%20owners%20and%20teaches%20in%20the%20family-business%20program%20at%20Saint%20Joseph's%20University%20in%20Pennsylvania.%20If%20that%20isn't%20an%20option%2C%20they%20look%20for%20someone%20they%20can%20trust%20to%20carry%20on%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoulam%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20Texas%20Renaissance%20Festival%2C%20is%20slightly%20older%20than%20the%20average%20boomer%20business%20owner%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20entering%20his%20late%2080s.%20But%20even%20he%20hasn't%20found%20a%20suitable%20buyer.%20His%20succession%20search%2C%20which%20was%20documented%20in%20the%20recent%20HBO%20series%20%26quot%3BRen%20Faire%2C%26quot%3B%20highlights%20the%20difficulty%20of%20passing%20along%20a%20business%20someone%20spent%20their%20whole%20life%20building.%20With%20small%20businesses%20especially%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20the%20numbers%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20very%20personal%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20for%20buyers%20able%20to%20find%20the%20right%20match%2C%20snatching%20up%20an%20existing%20business%20could%20be%20a%20smart%20move.%20For%20the%20Gutekunsts%2C%20one%20acquisition%20intended%20as%20a%20lifestyle%20change%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20collection%20of%20businesses%20built%20around%20southern%20Maine's%20deep%20tradition%20of%20woodcrafting.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20fun%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20Gutekunst%20tells%20me.%20It%20also%20beats%20not%20having%20a%20satisfying%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20I%20wrote%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-wealth-transfer-myth-dont-count-on-inheritance-estate-planning-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emyth%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Boomer%20Wealth%20Transfer%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20about%20how%20most%20boomers%20don't%20have%20many%20assets%20to%20pass%20along%2C%20and%20those%20that%20do%20are%20likely%20to%20get%20eaten%20up%20by%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20elder%20care.%20But%20even%20if%20you%20can't%20plan%20on%20receiving%20an%20inheritance%2C%20you%20can%20create%20one%20for%20yourself%20(and%20your%20own%20children).%20Buying%20up%20small%20businesses%20allows%20people%20without%20wealthy%20boomer%20parents%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20the%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20of%20wealth%20the%20generation%20is%20sitting%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fann-c-logue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAnn%20C.%20Logue%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20writer%20specializing%20in%20business%20and%20finance.%20She%20lives%20in%20Chicago.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-selling-small-businesses-investment-opportunity-millennials-gen-z-retirement-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727775662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f725a7de59ade1a3b58797%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-selling-sm