et%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20candidates%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20stand%20out%20and%20differentiate%20themselves%20in%20the%20application%20process.%20While%20DMing%20a%20recruiter%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20good%20idea%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20practically%20everyone's%20trying%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20cold%20DM%20probably%20won't%20yield%20a%20response%20from%20the%20CEO%20of%20Microsoft%20or%20Google%2C%20career%20coaches%20generally%20recommend%20this%20tactic%20for%20smaller%20to%20mid-tier%20companies%20where%20it's%20easier%20to%20get%20in%20front%20of%20the%20higher-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20career%20coaches%20in%20the%20tech%20space%20to%20hear%20about%20why%20candidates%20may%20want%20to%20try%20this%20new%20tactic.%20Here's%20what%20they%20had%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8dc51a6-f878-4f09-8935-a13e683fddf4%5C%22%3ERecruiter%20DMs%20are%20over-saturated%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKatie%20McIntyre%20is%20a%20career%20coach%20and%20co-owner%20at%20CareerSprout%2C%20which%20helps%20tech%20professionals%20land%20job%20offers%20in%20the%20%24200K%20to%20%24500K%20salary%20range.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20the%20current%20employer-driven%20market%2C%20applications%20have%20largely%20become%20%26quot%3Birrelevant%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20outreach%20messages%20are%20the%20most%20crowded%20CareerSprout%20has%20seen%20since%20it%20was%20founded%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20reach%20out%20to%20a%20recruiter%20directly%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20so%20have%20400%20other%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20McIntyre%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20getting%20the%20nuance%20of%20that%20down%20is%20really%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20led%20McIntyre%20to%20suggest%20reaching%20out%20to%20executives%20and%20potential%20hiring%20managers%20instead.%20She%20said%20this%20yields%20better%20response%20rates%20because%20there's%20likely%20to%20be%20significantly%20less%20traffic%20in%20a%20C-suite's%20DMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20has%20to%20be%20carefully%20curated%2C%20McIntyre%20added%2C%20but%20if%20done%20right%2C%20it%20can%20offer%20a%20better%20route%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222361835a-587a-48e7-8766-9d29c1cb7690%5C%22%3EExecutives%20may%20have%20a%20more%20nuanced%20understanding%20of%20technical%20skills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rajsubra.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaj%20Subrameyer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20%3Cspan%3Esenior%20IT%20manager%20and%20certified%20coach%20who%20offers%20career%20coaching%20services%20for%20mid%20to%20senior-level%20tech%20workers.%20He%20said%20that%20recruiters%20receive%20too%20many%20messages%20from%20candidates%20and%20may%3C%2Fspan%3E%20lack%20the%20technical%20expertise%20to%20discern%20subtle%20differences%20between%20applicants.%20Some%20tech%20workers%20have%20also%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-job-market-changed-interviews-companies-expect-llm-experience-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20are%20demanding%20increasingly%20specialized%3C%2Fa%3E%20skills%20and%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubrameyer%20said%20that%20candidates%20who%20get%20in%20front%20of%20an%20executive%20have%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20explaining%20the%20nuance%20of%20what%20they%20do.%20This%20can%20also%20be%20effective%20in%20situations%20where%20a%20worker%20hasn't%20been%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tech-jobs-basic-coding-programming-skills-education-needed-recruiters-2024-8%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRecruiters%2520say%2520these%2520positions%2520generally%2Cand%2520knowledge%2520of%2520AI%2520ethics.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-specific%20role%20before%20but%20has%20other%20experiences%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20demonstrate%20the%20skills%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenglish-literature-major-mit-opencourseware-ai-data-science-job-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20tech%20worker%20who%20studied%20English%20literature%20previously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20got%20her%20first%20two%20jobs%20out%20of%20college%20after%20reaching%20out%20to%20CEOs%20at%20the%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%20English%20background%20ended%20up%20being%20an%20asset%2C%20she%20might%20not%20have%20gotten%20the%20opportunity%20over%20someone%20who%20had%20a%20traditional%20tech%20background%20if%20she%20didn't%20get%20in%20front%20of%20the%20startup's%20CEO.%20In%20both%20situations%2C%20she%20was%20able%20to%20get%20an%20intro%20call%20with%20the%20CEO%20and%20landed%20a%20job%20offer%20after%20the%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2256e13f03-61be-4925-a45c-169664e7f213%5C%22%3EIt's%20not%20recommended%20for%20all%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20career%20coaches%20expressed%20mixed%20feelings%20on%20this%20new%20tactic%2C%20despite%20being%20approached%20about%20it%20by%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20one%20shot%20at%20a%20company%20is%20to%20message%20the%20CEO%20or%20hiring%20director%2C%20you're%20giving%20yourself%20a%20small%20window%20to%20sell%20yourself%20off%20one%20message%2C%26quot%3B%20Albano%20Gega%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20tech%20career%20coaching%20platform%20called%20Alza%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tactic%20could%20work%20for%20a%20smaller%20startup%2C%20Gega%20compared%20it%20to%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bhit%20a%20bull's-eye.%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-network-for-new-job-microsoft-vp-hr-explains-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20A%20better%20approach%20would%20be%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20people%20adjacent%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20position%20you're%20applying%20for%2C%20Gega%20said.%20Speaking%20to%20those%20kinds%20of%20employees%20can%20give%20more%20room%20for%20conversation%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20there's%20no%20magic%20formula%20to%20landing%20a%20tech%20job%20in%20this%20market%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20bad%20idea%20to%20think%20outside%20the%20box%20and%20get%20creative%20with%20your%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDesperate%20times%20need%20desperate%20measures%2C%26quot%3B%20Subrameyer%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20need%20to%20think%20out%20of%20the%20box%20on%20how%20to%20get%20noticed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-send-dm-ceo-hiring-director-executives-advice-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727771462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f98f887518aa57bc9f0d90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-send-dm-ceo-hiring-director-executives-advice-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20recruiters%20getting%20hundreds%20of%20DMs%2C%20a%20better%20way%20to%20get%20noticed%20at%20a%20small%20company%20may%20be%20by%20reaching%20out%20to%20its%20CEO.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-send-dm-ceo-hiring-director-executives-advice-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cannes%20Prizewinner%20Vimukthi%20Jayasundara%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Turtle%E2%80%99s%20Gaze%20on%20Spying%20Stars%E2%80%99%20Commences%20Shoot%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727771014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FNila-Madhab-Panda-Vimukthi-Jayasundara.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236161259%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sri%20Lankan%20auteur%C2%A0Vimukthi%20Jayasundara%2C%20whose%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Forsaken%20Land%E2%80%9D%20(200