%2Farticles%2Fc0jwqzzw986o%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bus%20was%20returning%20from%20a%20field%20trip%20when%20it%20crashed%20and%20caught%20fire%20just%20outside%20Bangkok.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A386%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jwqzzw986o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jwqzzw986o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jwqzzw986o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boeing's%20737%20safety%20mess%20just%20got%20worse%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225186%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Alaska%20Airlines%20Boeing%20737%20MAX%209%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fb64b77518aa57bc9f89d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223457%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Alaska%20Airlines%20Boeing%20737%20Max%209%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Carter%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20has%20more%20concerns%20about%20Boeing's%20planes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20said%20at%20least%2040%20airlines%20outside%20the%20US%20may%20be%20operating%20aircraft%20with%20risky%20rudder%20parts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20the%20latest%20blow%20to%20Boeing%2C%20which%20has%20been%20plagued%20by%20safety%20probes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20(NTSB)%20has%20flagged%20fresh%20concerns%20with%20Boeing's%20737%20planes%2C%20saying%20that%20at%20least%2040%20airlines%20outside%20the%20US%20may%20be%20operating%20aircraft%20with%20faulty%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NTSB%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ntsb.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2FPages%2FNR20240926.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%2C%20saying%20it%20had%20issued%20urgent%20safety%20recommendations%20to%20Boeing%20and%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20(FAA).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20said%20that%20the%20NTSB%20was%20investigating%20a%20February%206%20incident%20with%20a%20United%20Airlines%20Boeing%20737%20Max%208%20plane%2C%20which%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bstuck%26quot%3B%20rudder%20pedals%20while%20landing%20at%20Newark%20Liberty%20International%20Airport%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Board%20said%20that%20its%20investigators%20tested%20a%20rollout%20guidance%20actuator%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20rudder%20control%20components%20from%20the%20affected%20airplane%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20component's%20manufacturer%2C%20Collins%20Aerospace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20tested%20with%20another%20identical%20unit%20from%20a%20separate%20airplane%2C%20both%20actuators%20failed.%20Moisture%20was%20detected%20in%20both%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollins%20Aerospace%20later%20found%20that%20the%20sealed%20bearings%20on%20the%20units%20had%20been%20incorrectly%20assembled%2C%20%26quot%3Bleaving%20the%20unsealed%20side%20more%20susceptible%20to%20moisture%20that%20can%20freeze%20and%20limit%20rudder%20system%20movement%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NTSB%20said%20that%20Boeing's%20737%20flight%20manual%20instructs%20pilots%20facing%20a%20jammed%20rudder%20to%20overpower%20the%20system%20by%20applying%20%26quot%3Bmaximum%20force.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20Board%20warned%20that%20such%20force%20on%20faulty%20rudders%20could%20%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3Bunintentionally%20cause%20loss%20of%20control%20or%20departure%20from%20a%20runway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENTSB%20Chair%20Jennifer%20Homendy%20wrote%20a%C2%A0September%2030%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ntsb.gov%2Fnews%2FDocuments%2FBoeing%2520Urgent%2520Safety%2520Recommendations%2520ltr%2520to%2520FAA%2520Administrator.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20FAA's%20administrator%2C%20Michael%20Whitaker%2C%20saying%20she%20was%20concerned%20that%20the%20FAA%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20take%20this%20issue%20more%20seriously%20until%20we%20issued%20our%20urgent%20safety%20recommendation%20report.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20she%20had%20been%20made%20aware%20the%20%26quot%3BFAA%20has%20been%20downplaying%20the%20urgency%20of%20this%20issue%2C%20maintaining%20that%20the%20units%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomendy%20said%20that%20Boeing%20had%20said%20that%20it%20had%20received%20353%20affected%20actuator%20units%20since%20February%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Homendy's%20letter%2C%20271%20affected%20actuators%20may%20now%20be%20installed%20on%20aircraft%20in%20service%20operated%20by%20at%20least%2040%20foreign%20air%20carriers.%20She%20added%20that%2016%20units%20%26quot%3Bmay%20still%20be%20installed%20on%20US-registered%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomendy%20also%20slammed%20Boeing%20for%20failing%20to%20inform%20United%20Airlines%20that%20faulty%20actuators%20were%20installed%20in%20the%20737%20planes%20it%20had%20delivered%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20concerned%20of%20the%20possibility%20that%20other%20airlines%20are%20unaware%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20these%20actuators%20on%20their%20737%20airplanes%2C%26quot%3B%20Homendy%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20making%20operators%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20installed%20systems%20and%20equipment%20on%20the%20airplanes%20delivered%20to%20them%20is%20unacceptable%20and%20cannot%20continue%20to%20be%20tolerated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283df9e8e-4477-4580-94cb-f7372a1e0d82%5C%22%3EA%20bad%20look%20for%20Boeing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGuy%20Gratton%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20aviation%20and%20the%20environment%20at%20Cranfield%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20component%20faults%20reflect%20poorly%20on%20Boeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20another%20instance%20of%20national%20authorities%20in%20the%20USA%20(the%20Federation%20Aviation%20Administration%2C%20and%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board)%20stepping%20in%20to%20address%20safety%20issues%20that%20Boeing%20themselves%20should%20have%20already%20identified%20and%20rectified%2C%26quot%3B%20Gratton%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20anticipate%20their%20customers%20worldwide%20being%20disappointed%20in%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20added%20that%20he%20thought%20this%20issue%20was%20not%20as%20serious%20as%20Boeing's%20past%20safety%20issues%2C%20like%20the%20January%205%20incident%20when%20the%20door%20plug%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-boeing-737-max-9-door-blowout-company-response-earnings-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAlaska%20Airlines%20passenger%20plane%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20737%20Max%209%20model%20%E2%80%94%20detached%20during%20a%20flight%2C%20forcing%20pilots%20to%20make%20an%20emergency%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20fault%20could%20not%20in%20itself%20lead%20to%20loss%20of%20an%20aircraft%2C%20and%20even%20an%20aeroplane%20going%20off%20the%20side%20of%20a%20runway%2C%20whilst%20extremely%20embarrassing%20and%20expensive%2C%20would%20be%20unlikely%20to%20lead%20to%20loss%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Gratton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BI'd%20still%20be%20content%20to%20get%20into%20a%20Boeing%20737%2C%20and%20I%20do%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20does%20continue%20to%20show%20the%20company%20as%20being%20troubled%2C%20and%20its%20products%20less%20trustworthy%20than%20those%20of%20the%20obvious%20competitors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c23a3048-4c95-4c5b-8c89-bc8188352509%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELatest%20blow%20to%20an%20already%20beleaguered%20Boeing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20shares%20dropped%202.74%25%20on%20Monday.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20NTSB%20probe%20is%20the%20latest%20setback%20for%20the%20company.%20Their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-boeing-737-max-planes-have-issues-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMax%20family%20has%20been%20plagued%20by%20safety%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20two%20crashes%20of%20its%20737%20Max%20jetliners%20in%202018%20and%202019%20that%20killed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20total%20of%20346%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20following%20the%20Alaska%20Airlines%20door%20plug%20incident%2C%20the%20FAA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Ffaa-halts-boeing-max-production-expansion-improve-quality-control-also-lays-out-extensive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebarred%3C%2Fa%3E%20Boeing%20from%20expanding%20production%20on%20Max%20plane%20models%20until%20quality%20and%20safety%20issues%20were%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20string%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-whistleblower-says-he-saw-holes-drilled-wrongly-on-787s-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhistleblowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20alleged%20this%20year%20that%20the%20company%20is%20lax%20with%20safety%20and%20quality%20control.%20Some%20bombshell%20allegations%20were%20publicized%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hsgac.senate.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024.06.17-PSI-Majority-Staff-Memorandum.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esprawling%20204-page%20report%20released%20on%20June%2017%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Senate%20subcommittee%20that%20investigated%20Boeing's%20safety%20and%20quality%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20accounts%20include%20testimony%20from%20Sam%20Mohawk%2C%20a%20quality%20assurance%20inspector%20for%20Boeing%2C%20who%20alleged%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-whistleblower-faulty-plane-parts-may-be-on-new-aircraft-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecompany%20lost%20track%20of%20hundreds%20of%20faulty%20737%20parts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ordered%20staff%20to%20conceal%20improperly%20stored%20plane%20parts%20so%20FAA%20inspectors%20would%20not%20see%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerle%20Meyers%2C%20a%20former%20Boeing%20quality%20manager%2C%20said%20that%20Boeing's%20manufacturing%20team%20regularly%20tried%20to%20retrieve%20bad%20parts%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Breclamation%26quot%3B%20area%20even%20after%20they%20were%20thrown%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20BI's%20queries%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20defer%20to%20the%20NTSB%20on%20the%20investigation.%20The%20FAA%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%2C%20sent%20outside%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-safety-mess-just-got-worse-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727770422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fb6505f44bdb4cfa3864c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-safety-mess-just-got-worse-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20NTSB%20said%20at%20least%2040%20airlines%20outside%20the%20US%20may%20be%20operating%20aircraft%20with%20faulty%20rudder%20parts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abharade%40insider.com%20(Aditi%20Bharade)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-safety-mess-just-got-worse-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kirti%20Kumar%3A%20Bullet%20injured%20Govinda's%20toe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727770410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113843642%2Cimgsize-42470.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fb